1. That no man can tell the Future Event of things, no not for a day: and this comes to passe from the great vicissitude and unconstancy of all world
                  •
               y things. Or else, if I may but take in this Reason into the Proposition, then I shall run it thus;

One there is that is rais'd out of the Dust to sit among Princes: whereas there is another that is flung down from the pinnacle of worldly joy and prosperity, and stated, as Job was, upon the Dunghill.Ecelesiast. cap. 4. ver. 14. And this doth the Preacher tell us among the rest of those changes that fell under his observation, That one comes out of Prison to reign, (as Queen Elizabeth did out of the Tower to the Throne) whereas also there is he that is born in his Kingdome and becomes very poor;


